==English==
===Etymology===
Possibly a variant of Middle English [[shatter|schatteren]], from Old English ''sceaterian'', reflecting Norse influence.

===Transitive verb===
'''to scatter''' ([[scatters]], [[scattered]], [[scattering]])
#To cause to [[separate]] and go in different directions.
#To [[distribute]] [[loosely]] by or as if by [[sprinkle|sprinkling]]
#{{Physics}} To [[deflect]] (radiation or particles).

====Translations====
*Chinese Characters: [[渙]], [[涣]]
*French: disperser (1), éparpiller (2) parsemer (2)

===Intransitive verb===
#To separate and go in different directions; disperse.
#To occur or fall at widely spaced intervals.

